  <entry>
    <id>https://www.thunderbird.net/en-US/thunderbird/128.8.0esr/releasenotes/</id>
    <title type="html">Thunderbird 128.8.0esr</title>
    <author>
      <name>Thunderbird</name>
      <uri>https://www.thunderbird.net</uri>
    </author>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.thunderbird.net/en-US/thunderbird/128.8.0esr/releasenotes/"/>
    <updated>2025-03-05T00:00:00+00:00</updated>
    <published>2025-03-05T00:00:00+00:00</published>

    <content type="html"><![CDATA[
      

  
  

  
    

    
      
        
        

        
          <h3>Fixed</h3>
        

        
        
          <ul>
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Opening an .EML file in profiles with many folders could take a long time.</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Users with many folders experienced poor performance when resizing message panes.</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>"Replace" button in compose window was overwritten when the window was narrow.</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Export to mobile did not work when "Use default server" was selected.</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>"Save Link As" was not working in feed web content.</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p><a href="https://www.mozilla.org/en-US/security/known-vulnerabilities/thunderbird/#thunderbird128.8">Security fixes</a></p>
          
        </li>
      
    
    </ul>
  
  

<p>As always, you’re encouraged to <a href="https://connect.mozilla.org/t5/ideas/idb-p/ideas/label-name/thunderbird">tell us what you think</a>, <a href="https://support.mozilla.org/questions/new/thunderbird">ask for help</a>, or <a href="https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/enter_bug.cgi?product=Thunderbird">file a bug in Bugzilla</a></p>
